\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.1}{\ignorespaces How Retrieval-Augmented Generation grounds knowledge. Given a query, the system pulls Top-K relevant chunks from a knowledge base using hybrid search (BM25 + dense embeddings). Retrieved context merges with the query and feeds into the language model. This curbs hallucination and lets the system tap into current facts beyond its training cutoff, boosting factual accuracy 15--30\% on knowledge-heavy tasks.}}{64}{figure.caption.105}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:rag_architecture}{{5.1}{64}{How Retrieval-Augmented Generation grounds knowledge. Given a query, the system pulls Top-K relevant chunks from a knowledge base using hybrid search (BM25 + dense embeddings). Retrieved context merges with the query and feeds into the language model. This curbs hallucination and lets the system tap into current facts beyond its training cutoff, boosting factual accuracy 15--30\% on knowledge-heavy tasks}{figure.caption.105}{}}
