\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {14.2}{\ignorespaces GSM8K training curves for all four models. Qwen3-8B (base) demonstrates a characteristic RL emergence/phase transition around steps 22--25, jumping from $\sim $13\% to $\sim $78\% in five steps before saturating at 100\%. Llama-3.2-3B (dashed) is the negative result: reward never exceeds 2\% because the model lacks the minimum capacity to generate any correct solutions, leaving GRPO with no positive signal to learn from.}}{113}{figure.caption.160}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:gsm8k_curves}{{14.2}{113}{GSM8K training curves for all four models. Qwen3-8B (base) demonstrates a characteristic RL emergence/phase transition around steps 22--25, jumping from $\sim $13\% to $\sim $78\% in five steps before saturating at 100\%. Llama-3.2-3B (dashed) is the negative result: reward never exceeds 2\% because the model lacks the minimum capacity to generate any correct solutions, leaving GRPO with no positive signal to learn from}{figure.caption.160}{}}
